main event: A civilian in Cincinnati, Ohio reported an unidentified aerial phenomenon on April 6, 1969 between 7:30 AM and 7:55 AM.
interesting points: The report form indicates that there was insufficient data to draw a conclusion about the sighting.
The observer was instructed to complete an AF Form 117 and return it to provide more information for a scientific investigation.
The document includes a diagram or sketch the observer was supposed to use to indicate the position and elevation of the observed phenomenon.
The form asked detailed questions about the characteristics and movement of the observed object, such as whether it moved in a straight line, hovered, changed color or brightness, etc.
The observer reported that the phenomenon 'faded out' periodically during the 7-8 minute sighting.
